# Next.js / React

- Use the **App Router** layout under **`apps/web/app/`** with `page.tsx`, `layout.tsx`, `loading.tsx`, `error.tsx` as appropriate.
- Prefer **named exports** for components when the file already follows that pattern; stay consistent with neighboring files.
- Keep frontend layer separation strict:
  - `.tsx` files are for view structure/composition.
  - `.ts` files are for reusable logic/helpers (formatters, selectors, mappers).
  - Web styles live in `.css`/`.module.css`.
- **Web UI**: Shared DOM components live in **`@portfolio/web-ui`** (`packages/web-ui/src/`). Import from the app as **`@portfolio/web-ui`** (and package CSS subpaths). Do not add new `components/` for web UI; ESLint enforces this.
- For **`apps/web/lib/cv-pdf/**`**, keep styles in react-pdf `StyleSheet` files (`styles.ts`) and do not migrate PDF styles to web CSS.
- **Data fetching**: Prefer server-side fetching in Server Components; use `fetch` caching defaults intentionally. For client mutations, use patterns already present in the repo (e.g. Server Actions, route handlers).
- **Metadata**: Use the Metadata API (`export const metadata` or `generateMetadata`) for SEO and social cards instead of ad-hoc `<head>` manipulation where possible.
- **Imports**: Use path aliases if `tsconfig` defines them; otherwise relative imports — match existing style.
- Run **`yarn lint`** and **`yarn build`** (or project-documented equivalents) after non-trivial changes; see skill `nextjs-change-checklist`.
